88
00:04:21,420 --> 00:04:23,360
Is she taking care of the patient?

89
00:04:23,900 --> 00:04:25,680
Maybe I should go there.

90
00:04:28,540 --> 00:04:29,440
Linlang.

91
00:04:30,860 --> 00:04:32,180
Ms. Tang has worked here

92
00:04:32,180 --> 00:04:33,040
for half a year.

93
00:04:34,660 --> 00:04:35,720
Let me ask you,

94
00:04:36,500 --> 00:04:37,500
what kind of person

95
00:04:37,500 --> 00:04:38,660
do you think

96
00:04:38,660 --> 00:04:40,120
Ms. Tang is at work?

97
00:04:42,140 --> 00:04:43,360
She's hard-working

98
00:04:43,780 --> 00:04:44,920
and professional.

99
00:04:45,420 --> 00:04:47,320
She doesn't avoid responsibilities.

100
00:04:49,220 --> 00:04:50,500
Then do you think it's impossible

101
00:04:50,500 --> 00:04:51,710
that such a person would take a day off

102
00:04:51,710 --> 00:04:53,040
without leaving any messages?

103
00:04:59,620 --> 00:05:00,520
I get it.

104
00:05:01,220 --> 00:05:02,120
Thanks, Ms. Qin.

105
00:05:02,540 --> 00:05:03,760
I know what to do.

106
00:05:06,260 --> 00:05:07,100
Linlang.

107
00:05:07,820 --> 00:05:09,600
Did you find many problems

108
00:05:09,820 --> 00:05:11,280
during the parallel session of the case?

109
00:05:12,100 --> 00:05:12,940
Yes.

110
00:05:12,980 --> 00:05:15,360
